To create a Discord bot using Discord.js v14, you will need to have Node.js installed on your local machine. Here is an example code that creates a bot with a single command, "ban". The bot has a slash command to ban a user.

**Note**: Before you start, make sure to replace `YOUR_BOT_TOKEN` with your bot's actual token.

```javascript
const Discord = require('discord.js');
const client = new Discord.Client();

const token = process.env.DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN; // replace with your bot token

// Set up event listeners
client.on('messageCreate', (message) => {
    if (message.author.id === client.user.id) return;

    if (message.content.startsWith('/ban')) {
        const [username, reason] = message.content.split(' ');
        const user = message.mentions.members.first() || message.author;

        user.ban({
            reason: reason,
            time: '10',
            member: user
        })
       .then(() => {
            console.log(`Banned ${username} for ${reason} (${user.name}#${user.discriminator})`);
        })
       .catch((err) => {
            console.error('Failed to ban user:', err);
        });
    }
});

client.login(token);

client.on('error', (err) => {
    console.error('There was an error logging in to the bot:', err);
});
```

This code uses the `Discord.js` library to interact with the Discord API and bans the user that sends the `/ban` command. The `client.login(token)` call logs the bot in and starts the event loop.

Make sure to replace `YOUR_BOT_TOKEN` with your bot's actual token.

